he business, and it is prudent to take such mitigating measures on the part of the business to reduce the risk. The organization can design a proactive style to eliminate legal impediments by creating a culture of providing opportunities for communication between&nbsp; stakeholders so that they can understand how the business entity operates (customers, vendors, contractual partners, and regulatory bodies). Transparency is critical to building trust and achieving mutually beneficial relationships. A clear and precise explanation of the company policies, rules, and customer expectations can reduce the risk of conflicts for clients. The quality commitment to the contracts and the agreements, which are well written without ambiguity and are certainly reviewed by legal counsel, helps in the reduction of contractual disputes with appellants or affiliations (Bellavitis et al., 2019). Closely communicating with regulatory agencies while keeping up to date on changing regulations is also essential for businesses to pick up on emerging trends and issues while avoiding fines or litigations.</p>', '', NULL, NULL, 'Poet Cruz', 'poetcruz.pc@gmail.com', '2024-05-03 17:00:00', 375, '2.00', 'Completed', '2024-05-01 22:20:12', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 1, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-10 04:41:40', '2024-05-11 10:51:50', '2025-05-24 11:08:48', 0, NULL, NULL);
