(10221, 'tt', 'test', 'tt', '<p>Climate change also intensifies extreme weather events, including hurricanes, droughts, and wildfires. For instance, hurricanes fueled by warmer ocean waters have become more powerful and destructive, as evidenced by recent storms in the Atlantic. Prolonged droughts in regions like Sub-Saharan Africa threaten food security, while wildfires in Australia and California highlight the dangers posed to both ecosystems and human settlements.</p><p>Biodiversity is another casualty of climate change. Rising <a href=\\\"http://localhost/falcon.sub/sudo/create-task\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">temperatures </a>and shifting habitats disrupt ecosystems, leading to species migration, extinction, and reduced biodiversity. Coral reefs, which support marine life and protect coastlines, are under threat from ocean warming and acidification.<img src=\\\"data:image/jpeg;base64,', '', NULL, NULL, 'Sue', 'poultrysue@gmail.com', '2025-05-22 13:31:00', 375, '3.00', 'Completed', '2025-05-21 17:31:43', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2025-05-21 20:31:43', 1, 'taskfiles/submissions/1749307322_MG 116 DEI Reflection Assignment- Fall 2023.pdf,taskfiles/submissions/1749307720_WhatsApp Image 2023-11-14 at 19.13.44 (2).jpeg', 'https://monkbrian.sfo3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/taskfiles/submissions/1749307720_WhatsApp Image 2023-11-14 at 19.13.44 (2).jpeg', '27948,60545', '2025-06-07 17:48:44', '2025-07-31 12:25:12', '2025-07-31 12:25:45', '2025-07-31 09:25:45', 0, NULL, NULL);
